DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros("PG.pl", "PGbasicmacros.pl", "PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl");

install_problem_grader(~~&std_problem_grader);
TEXT(&beginproblem);

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;
$showPartialCredit = 0;

# output the text of the problem

$a = random(20,50,1);
$b = random(10,20,1);
$c = random(20,50,1);
$d = random(10,20,1);
$co1 = $c+$d;
$co2 = $a+$b;

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

The consumers will demand $a units when the price of a product is $DOLLAR$co1,
and $co2 units when the price is $DOLLAR$c. Find the demand function 
(express thr price \( p \) in terms of the quantity \( q \)), assuming it is 
linear.

\( p= \) \{ans_rule(30)\}        

EOT

$ans = "-$d/$b(q-$a)+$c+$d";

&ANS(multivar_function_cmp($ans,"q"));


